{"id":787798,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Igor_Maslennikov","text":"Igor Fyodorovich Maslennikov (; born 26 October 1931) is a Soviet and Russian movie director and screenwriter. He was born in Nizhny Novgorod, Soviet Union.\nHis career lasted between 1967 to 2002. He directed the movies \"Under en steinhimmel\", \"Winter Cherry\", \"The Queen of Spades\" and \"Tomorrow, on April 3rd...\".\nIn 2001 he was a member of the jury at the 23rd Moscow International Film Festival.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Soviet_Union","surface_form":"Soviet","offset":59},{"uri":"Russia","surface_form":"Russia","offset":70},{"uri":"Movie__director","surface_form":"movie director","offset":78},{"uri":"Screenwriter","surface_form":"screenwriter","offset":97},{"uri":"Nizhny_Novgorod","surface_form":"Nizhny Novgorod","offset":126},{"uri":"Soviet_Union","surface_form":"Soviet Union","offset":143},{"uri":"Under_en_steinhimmel","surface_form":"Under en steinhimmel","offset":221},{"uri":"Winter_Cherry","surface_form":"Winter Cherry","offset":245},{"uri":"The_Queen_of_Spades_(1982_movie)","surface_form":"The Queen of Spades","offset":262},{"uri":"Tomorrow%2C_on_April_3rd...","surface_form":"Tomorrow, on April 3rd...","offset":288},{"uri":"Moscow_International_Film_Festival","surface_form":"Moscow International Film Festival","offset":364}]}